column5: hey guys, just got back from the temagami spring trip and let me tell you i worked my but off trying to catch those walleye.. i searched my usual spots and nothing..i asked some locals who told me fishing was tough do to the crazy weather they have been having..i can tell you it was unusual not to see one blackfly or mosquito..so i started looking at water temps and finally found them holding tight to the shore..yup still in post spawn they were..so i began to cast every shore line, shoal, fallen trees and widy points and they she was, she was empty and probaly starving...   here is another one caught from  my buddy mike who usually does well but only got one this year.. as you can see weather was awsome    the walleye were beat up comming off of spawn as you can see the tail on this walleye..it was badly ripped from spawn  all in all i would say we did pretty well on the walleye considerin most people wer not catching them..and yes we ate them and they were GOOOD !!!         also found me some pike and a laker.. the laker was caught jigging in 65 feet of water.. i got 4 lakers jigging and none trolling..most people trolling this week had hard time catching lakers..even though the screen was full of them      got me a couple more doing the same thing.. caught 1 walleye per 200 hundred casts..did i mention it was tough fishing???        all i can say is i cant wait for august...and feb ice fishing..lol
nice going  good to see you figured out where they were
..oh.. GLAD  you had a good trip Rob! lol  Can be a tough lake at many times... oh.. and I know that spot!  I might get there by months end...
Looks like a great trip.  Thanks for sharing.  Have not been on that lake in ages....
Holy Fish!!! Great job man, must be tasty haha  Thanks for sharing, MTBF
Nice fish. Heading up in 3 weeks. Can you share what baits you were using?
nice report... hopefully they are not as hard to find in sept.
all i can tell you is pink jig heads worked great this year and always tip them with a little meat...
